parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to become spongy or go to the floor, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distances, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle pulls to one side when applying the brakes
the brakes are unresponsive or delayed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake positioner can cause the brake pedal to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to brake, which can lead to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes stuck
the brake pedal is difficult to press
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Seat Belts and Airbags to Deploy in Crash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of seat belts to restrain occupants and airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Seat belts fail to restrain occupants
airbags fail to deploy upon impact
occupants experience injuries despite being seated and buckled up.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Sway Bar Link Failure/Loss of Vehicle Stability
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sway bar link can cause a loss of vehicle stability, making it difficult to control the vehicle, especially in high winds or during sudden maneuvers, which can lead to accidents or rollovers.
symptoms: The vehicle fishtails or sways excessively
the vehicle is difficult to control
especially in high winds or during sudden maneuvers
the vehicle's rear end feels unstable or loose
the vehicle's steering feels unresponsive or vague.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the rear axle from the vehicle can cause a loss of braking ability, leading to accidents and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Sudden loss of braking ability
unusual noise or vibration from the rear of the vehicle
visible signs of axle separation (e.g. broken or damaged components)
front wheels disengaging from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries. In this case, the fire was extinguished, but the vehicle was still severely damaged.
symptoms: The air conditioning unit distributes hot air
white smoke emerges from the engine compartment
the vehicle catches fire
and there may be a lack of warning indicator lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The air conditioning unit distributes hot air
reduced airflow from the vents
or unusual noises from the AC system.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The absence of warning indicator lights can prevent the driver from being alerted to potential issues, leading to delayed response or failure to address the problem, which can result in more severe consequences.
symptoms: No warning lights or indicators illuminate on the dashboard despite the presence of a malfunction or failure.
